title: The Naval War of 1812
creator: Theodore Roosevelt
description: LibriVox recording of THE NAVAL WAR OF 1812, by THEODORE ROOSEVELT. Read by James Carson. Somewhat detailed history of naval engagements between the United States and England during the War of 1812, from a decidely American perspective. Completed by the author as a young man at age 24. After 120 years, it remains a standard study of the war. (Summary by JCarson) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; history; war; navy
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Very long, but the stories are interesting, stories told from many perspectives. I've listened to it twice, & am looking forward to a third time.
